const principles = [
  {
    title: 'Context is a resource, not a log.',
    body: 'Treat memory like infrastructure: explicit, bounded, and routable. Sloppy context produces sloppy results. The discipline that makes distributed systems reliable is the same discipline that makes AI workflows reliable.',
    source: 'Fillory AI',
  },
  {
    title: 'Measure before you optimize.',
    body: 'The Nav Menu worked perfectly — until 7-second load times made it unusable. Correctness without performance is a prototype. Ship the measurement instrumentation before you ship the feature.',
    source: 'Prosper IT',
  },
  {
    title: 'Behavioral verification isn\'t optional for AI systems.',
    body: 'Agents drift. They go sycophantic. Testing for functional correctness is not the same as testing for behavioral alignment. The two failure modes don\'t even look like failures — they look like the system doing its job.',
    source: 'Fillory AI',
  },
  {
    title: 'Security belongs at the boundary, not sprinkled everywhere.',
    body: 'Validate at entry points. Trust the interior. Adding validation to every internal function doesn\'t create defense in depth — it creates noise that obscures where the real boundaries are.',
    source: 'Office Ally',
  },
  {
    title: 'Good documentation compounds team velocity.',
    body: 'Offshore team reviews, clear API contracts, structured handoff protocols — these aren\'t overhead. They\'re multipliers. Every hour spent writing a clear spec saves three hours of clarifying questions across timezone gaps.',
    source: 'Office Ally',
  },
  {
    title: 'The fastest fix is sometimes the most destructive one.',
    body: 'An agent optimizing for quick resolution will identify constraints as obstacles. Those constraints are often the architecture. "Easy" and "correct" are not the same objective — recognizing when they diverge is the actual skill.',
    source: 'Fillory AI',
  },
